grave, Leicestershire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Belgrave","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from a place in Leicestershire, recorded in Domesday Book as <i>Merdegrave</i>. The original name derived from Old English <i>mearth</i> ‘marten’ + <i>grāf</i> ‘grove’, but after the Norman Conquest the first element was taken to be Old French <i>merde</i> ‘dung, filth’, and changed to Old French <i>beu</i>, <i>bel</i> ‘fair, lovely’, to remove the unpleasant association. A mid 12th-century writer refers to the place as ‘<i>Merthegrave, nunc</i> (now) <i>Belegrava</i>’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":75,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":84,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":119,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Sir William de Belgrave was born about 1140, in Belgrave, Leicestershire, England. He had at least 1 son with Mrs. William de Belgrave."},"et":{"about 1140–Deceased":"umbes 1140–Surnud","1150–Female":"1150–Surnud","1190–Male":"1190–Surnud","1140–Male":"1140–Surnud","1190":"1190","about 1140":"umbes 1140","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1140":"1140","1150":"1150","Belgrave, Leicestershire, England":"Belgrave, Leicestershire, England"},"fi":{"about 1140–Deceased":"noin 1140–Kuollut","1150–Female":"1150–Kuollut","1190–Male":"1190–Kuollut","1140–Male":"1140–Kuollut","1190":"1190","about 1140":"noin 1140","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1140":"1140","1150":"1150","Belgrave, Leicestershire, England":"Belgrave, Leicestershire, England"},"fr":{"about 1140–Deceased":"environ 1140–Décédé","1150–Female":"1150–Décédée","1190–Male":"1190–Décédé","1140–Male":"1140–Décédé","1190":"1190","about 1140":"environ 1140","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1140":"1140","1150":"1150","Belgrave, Leicestershire, England":"Belgrave, Leicestershire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Sir William de Belgrave est né environ 1140, à Belgrave, Lei